# MASTER PROMPT — MTK GALLERY BUILDER

Act as a senior Vanilla JavaScript application architect and production UI/UX engineer.

Build a complete gallery application named `mtk-gallery` for selling hand-painted artwork.

Use this repository as the base:
https://github.com/NYCMEL/nala-website.git

Use all wc code for include, subscribe, publish, wc-include, etc from:
https://github.com/NYCMEL/nala-website/js/_wc.js

--------------------------------------------------
# OUTPUT RULES
--------------------------------------------------

* Return ONLY one downloadable ZIP file named exactly: `x.zip`
* Never show code in chat
* Never return patch files or diffs
* Always return complete files only
* Never modify anything outside the scope of this request
* Never generate placeholder explanations instead of files
* Never create images unless explicitly requested

--------------------------------------------------
# REQUIRED FILES
--------------------------------------------------

Generate exactly these files:

* mtk-gallery.config.js
* mtk-gallery.scss
* mtk-gallery.html
* mtk-gallery.js
* index.html

No server.
All item information must come from:
`mtk-gallery.config.js`

Only create additional files if absolutely required for functionality.

--------------------------------------------------
# CORE TECH RULES
--------------------------------------------------

* Vanilla JavaScript only
* No frameworks
* No Bootstrap
* No React
* No Vue
* No Angular
* No external libraries
* No inline JavaScript
* No inline styles
* SCSS only
* Never compile CSS except:
  * index.html may use CSS directly
* Never use iframes
* Use:
  <wc-include href="..."></wc-include>

--------------------------------------------------
# COMPONENT ARCHITECTURE
--------------------------------------------------

Component wrapper:

<mtk-gallery class="mtk-gallery"></mtk-gallery>

Rules:

* Root class must be `.mtk-gallery`
* Scope ALL styles under `.mtk-gallery`
* No global styles
* No global IDs
* Use semantic HTML only
* ADA compliant
* Keyboard accessible
* Responsive design
* Visible focus states required

--------------------------------------------------
# CONFIG + DATA RULES
--------------------------------------------------

ALL UI-driven data MUST come from:
`mtk-gallery.config.js`

Paintings must support:

* artwork ID
* title
* description
* image
* price
* availability
* dimensions
* medium
* category
* PayPal data

Store owner must be able to:

* change paintings
* change prices
* change availability
* change images
* change details

from either:

* config file
* SQLite database

--------------------------------------------------
# EVENT SYSTEM RULES
--------------------------------------------------

Wait for `<mtk-gallery>` to exist before initializing because it may load dynamically through `<wc-include>`.

Requirements:

* Subscribe to all `4-mtk-gallery` events using `wc.subscribe`
* Create `onMessage()` handler
* Publish actions using `wc.publish`
* Log ALL payloads using `wc.log` BEFORE publishing

--------------------------------------------------
# GALLERY UI
--------------------------------------------------

Header title:
`Madam Mina's Artwork`

Header requirements:

* Full page width
* Sticky header
* Material Design style
* Mint background color: `#55efc4`
* Drop shadow
* Margin-bottom: 25px
* Smooth fade-out of subtitle/description on scroll
* NO flickering on scroll
* Remove top padding/margin gaps

Header content:

* Title
* Subtitle
* Config-driven description

Description:

Madam Mina’s Artwork showcases original hand-painted creations inspired by emotion, culture, texture, and timeless artistic expression. Each piece is thoughtfully crafted to bring warmth, elegance, and personality into modern living spaces, offering collectors unique artwork designed to inspire conversation and lasting visual impact.

--------------------------------------------------
# HOME SCREEN
--------------------------------------------------

* Display painting cards only
* NO buttons on cards

Painting click behavior:

* Opens full-page detail view

Detail view includes:

* image
* title
* description
* price
* availability
* dimensions
* medium
* actions

Include circular close button with “X”

--------------------------------------------------
# SALES + REQUEST FLOWS
--------------------------------------------------

Available paintings:

Show:

* Buy with PayPal
* “Make me a counter offer”

Unavailable paintings:

Show status as:

* Sold

Show:

* “Request a similar painting”

Behavior:

* Clicking links reveals forms
* Forms hidden by default

--------------------------------------------------
# FORM DESIGN RULES
--------------------------------------------------

Use Material Design styling for:

* floating labels
* buttons
* fields
* spacing
* focus states
* hover states
* accessibility states

Forms must feel modern and production-ready.

--------------------------------------------------
# ADMIN FEATURES
--------------------------------------------------

Customers:

* NO login required

Admin:

* Login visible ONLY when admin chooses to manage/edit

Temporary credentials:

* username: admin
* password: test

Admin requirements:

* Login fields auto-filled with:
  * admin
  * test

* Add paintings
* Edit paintings
* Remove paintings
* Export gallery
* Persist changes to SQLite

--------------------------------------------------
# ADMIN SCREEN RULES
--------------------------------------------------

VERY IMPORTANT:

Admin screen must ONLY display ONE MODE at a time:

--------------------------------------------------
LIST MODE
--------------------------------------------------

Show ONLY:

* Artwork list
* New Artwork button
* Export Gallery button
* Logout button

Do NOT show form in list mode.

--------------------------------------------------
FORM MODE
--------------------------------------------------

Show ONLY:

* Artwork form
* Cancel button
* Logout button

Do NOT show artwork list in form mode.

--------------------------------------------------
NEW ARTWORK MODE
--------------------------------------------------

When creating a new artwork:

* Show black placeholder image panel on LEFT
* Center text:
  "NO IMAGE YET!"

--------------------------------------------------
EDIT MODE
--------------------------------------------------

When editing artwork:

* Show artwork image on LEFT
* Show form on RIGHT

--------------------------------------------------
IMAGE PATH RULES
--------------------------------------------------

DO NOT:

* Convert images to data:image base64

ONLY use:

* Relative paths from:
  ./img/

Examples:

* ./img/mel.png
* ./img/art-1001.jpg

Image field:

* Must accept relative image paths
* Must NOT use HTML input type=url
* Must allow:
  * ./img/file.jpg
  * img/file.jpg
  * https://...

--------------------------------------------------
FOOTER
--------------------------------------------------

Footer requirements:

* Full width
* Same mint color as header
* Compact height
* Small text only

Footer content:

Contact me: MadamMinaArts@gmail.com

Email must be clickable.

--------------------------------------------------
FAILURE PREVENTION RULES
--------------------------------------------------

DO NOT:

* use placeholder code
* omit required files
* generate partial implementations
* break existing requirements
* replace Vanilla JS with frameworks
* compile SCSS into CSS
* expose passwords in UI
* create empty SQLite DB structure without tables
* create fake API routes

Ensure ALL generated files are runnable together.

--------------------------------------------------
# FINAL DELIVERY RULES
--------------------------------------------------

Return ONLY:

* downloadable ZIP file
* named exactly `x.zip`

Do NOT:

* explain code
* summarize code
* paste snippets
* show partial implementations
